21/07/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- The ruling Democratic Party (DP) insisted on Sunday (July 20th) that the opposition participate in drafting a law on opening the files of the former state security services' employees. DP lawmaker Gjok Vuksani called on opposition parties to join the ruling party's initiative. "Anyone who is clean will come out clean. The opposition does not have to be afraid of verification," he said. (Koha Jone, News 24, Shekulli - 21/07/08)
